<hl>
<seg id=1> Financial Minister of Cote d'Ivoire Said West Africa's Economic Growth Reverted Remarkably </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Abidjan, January 18 (Journalist Linhu Daocheng) - Cote d'Ivoire economic and financial minister Engolan said here on 17, the economic growth of the entire member countries of Economic and Monetary Union of Western Africa has been reverted remarkably, and their major economic elements show a good condition. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Engolan said on an economic personnel symposium sponsored by France - Cote d'Ivoire Merchant Club, the economic growth rate of the entire member countries of Economic and Monetary Union of Western Africa reverted to 5.9% in 1996, 6.3% in 1997, while in 1994 it was only 2.6%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said, in recent years, West African countries have greatly improved the situation of import and export unbalance and public investment, increased the favorable balance of trade significantly; meanwhile, the budget deficit was decreased considerably to only 1.3% of GDP in these countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> When talking about the impact of Euro system, that to be put into practice by Europe Union, on African Franc, Engolan expressed that it is not necessary to worry about African Franc's future. </seg>
<seg id=6> He said, because the economy growth of the entire member countries of Economic and Monetary Union of Western Africa has reverted remarkably, the Africa Franc will not devaluate sharply by 50% in a short period of time like that happened in January 1994. </seg>
</p>
